      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANNYKEV (4) finished off nicely behind a smart one last time out in much stronger company. Back to this grade is a big tick for his chances following a strong win in a CL1 two back. Pike remains in the saddle here, it sets up nicely for him and if he runs up to his latest performance, he can get back to winning ways. LUCKY I AM (5) has been caught late in the race throughout her campaign, but faces an easier assignment this time around. She should find the front from an inside barrier, with Cooper's 2kg claim coming in handy. Will be very hard to run down. INFLUENCING (1) will be fitter for a recent trial and he is a first-up winner in the past. This looks to set up nicely for him from a good draw and with Nottle's claim. Can put his best foot forward. SNOW PRINCE (2) hasn't been far away in recent races and can be thereabouts once again. SOLDIER OF GOD (8) missed narrowly at Ascot last time out and rates highly on the back of that effort.",
